QUALIFICATION: the name Ricinula appeared in the heading of plate 395, which depicts 7 different species, none of which is named. Lamarck [1822, Histoire naturelle des animaux sans vertèbres, 7: 230-233] named these 7 species, and two additional ones, in Ricinula. Gray, 1847, Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 15: 139, designated Murex neritoideus, and Cossmann, 1903, Essais de paléoconchologie comparée, 5: 79, designated Murex ricinus Linnaeus as type species of Ricinula. Neither Murex neritoideus nor Murex ricinus were originally included species. QUALIFICATION: the Genera of Recent Mollusca, 1: 126; Name attributed to Klein and used as a senior synonym of Thais Bolten. Under Art. 11.5, not available from Bruguière [1792, Encyclopédie méthodique. Histoire naturelle des vers, 1(2): 530], who merely presented Klein's system without adopting it. Sowerby [1839, A conchological manual: 107] also had a dictionary entry for Tribulus Klein. Ricinula, Lam.; however, he had an entry for Ricinula on p. 92-93; Ricinula was used as a valid name, and the context indicates that Sowerby did not use Tribulus as a valid name. Herrmannsen [1849, Indicis generum malacozoorum primordia, 2: 587] also had an entry for Tribulus Klein which is listed as equivalent to Ricinula Lamarck. Under Art. 11.6.2, neither of these constitute an available establishment of Tribulus. Senior objective synonym of Planithais
